The paper deals with the problem of minimising DFAs, which is a fundamental topic in formal languages and automata theory, hence cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents algorithms and complexity results, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of logarithmic functions in the time complexity suggests that the paper may also be related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the difficulty of decision problems, which is a topic in logic and computation (cs.LO).
